notesStmt.note: This seminar discussion is part of a summer school and takes place among European, Asian and North American students on the topic of combating terrorism. During the preceding phase of the seminar, the students were asked to split into six groups and to choose an international organization or a government/country and to come up with some suggestions as to what this organization/government could to do to act against terrorism. In this final part of the seminar, students (as representatives of the six groups) report on their subgroups' suggestions. The ideas presented are then discussed by the whole seminar group. The short presentations given for this purpose are entirely non-scripted and quite spontaneous, as the discussions that are reported on took place immediately before this event. The whole seminar group consists of about 40 people, however, not all of them actively participate in this particular event. Since the seminar takes place in a larger hall, the event was recorded on two MD-players in order to get good quality recordings that capture speakers sitting in different parts of the room. Due to the size of the group, background noises, murmuring and whispering can be heard from time to time, but these are normally not represented in the transcription unless they become relevant for the main interaction. Generally, a very friendly atmosphere prevails.
